criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  (1) patients with established cardiovascular disease (unstable angina or stroke in the
             previous 3 to 12 months, and left ventricular ejection fraction ≥50%);

          -  (2) diagnosis of moderate to severe generalized periodontitis (PD>5mm and marginal
             bone loss >30% on at least 50% of the teeth, according to Tonetti et al. 2007);

          -  (3) presence of at least 3 teeth per quadrant.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  (1) periodontal treatment in the previous year;

          -  (2) antibiotic intake in the previous 3 months;

          -  (3) smokers of ≥10 cigarettes per day;

          -  (4) pregnancy or breast feeding;

          -  (5) diabetes mellitus types I or II, with glycosylated hemoglobin values >7;

          -  (6) necrotizing periodontal diseases;

          -  (7) HIV infection;

          -  (8) chronic intake of NSAID
